President Obama has announced the selection of Avril Haines as his Deputy National Security Advisor. Haines has been a key member of the national security team since the beginning of the Administration, serving as the National Security Council's Legal Advisor and currently as the Deputy Director of the Central Intelligence Agency. She is known for her intelligence, work ethic, and humility, and has worked in positions across the three branches of government. President Obama expresses his trust and confidence in Haines and believes she will continue to play a critical role in keeping the nation secure and promoting American interests and values worldwide. The President also thanks and commends Antony Blinken, who was confirmed as Deputy Secretary of State, and looks forward to continuing to work with him in his new role.